<Link id="l00913" /><CodeLine lineNumber="913"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Pseudo probes are like debug instructions which do not turn into real</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00914" /><CodeLine lineNumber="914"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// machine code. We try to use the function to skip both debug instructions</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00915" /><CodeLine lineNumber="915"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// and pseudo probe operations to avoid API proliferation. This should work</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00916" /><CodeLine lineNumber="916"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// most of the time when considering optimizing the rest of code in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00917" /><CodeLine lineNumber="917"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// block, except for certain cases where pseudo probes are designed to block</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00918" /><CodeLine lineNumber="918"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// the optimizations. For example, code merge like optimizations are supposed</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00919" /><CodeLine lineNumber="919"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// to be blocked by pseudo probes for better AutoFDO profile quality.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00920" /><CodeLine lineNumber="920"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// Therefore, they should be considered as a valid instruction when this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00921" /><CodeLine lineNumber="921"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// function is called in a context of such optimizations. On the other hand,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00922" /><CodeLine lineNumber="922"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// \\c SkipPseudoOp should be true when it&#39;s used in optimizations that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00923" /><CodeLine lineNumber="923"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// unlikely hurt profile quality, e.g., without block merging. The default</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00924" /><CodeLine lineNumber="924"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// value of \\c SkipPseudoOp is set to true to maximize code quality in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00925" /><CodeLine lineNumber="925"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// general, with an explict false value passed in in a few places like branch</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00926" /><CodeLine lineNumber="926"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  /// folding and if-conversion to favor profile quality.</span></CodeLine>
